Define `subprocess_text_output` in zulip_tools.py like this:

``` py
def subprocess_text_output(args):
    return subprocess.check_output(args, universal_newlines=True).strip()
```

and use it instead of `subprocess.check_output`. This reduces ugliness as discussed in https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/1168#issuecomment-230344313.

